    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and
        Camshaft - Removal - Camshaft Bushings
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Camshaft Bushings</title>
        <figure id="f3350016512" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK03/K03013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Camshaft Bushing Puller (installer)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Puller screw</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pulling nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Thrust bearing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pulling plate</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pulling spacer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Extension tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Puller screw extension</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Expanding collet</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Backup nut</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Although the inside diameter of each camshaft bushing is the same, the outside diameters and
                    widths are different depending on bushing location. See crankcase and camshaft bushing
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_426.xml" xrefid="t335001601">Specifications</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001601"/>.
                </para>
                <para>Use
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_428.xml" xrefid="t335001603">Camshaft Bushing Puller</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001603"/>
                    to remove camshaft bushings. Remove the front and rear camshaft bushings first. Remove the camshaft
                    seal ring and rear camshaft bushing from the rear of the crankcase.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble the correct expanding collet and backup nut on the puller screw extension. See
                camshaft bushing
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_426.xml" xrefid="t335001601">Specifications</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001601"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350016513" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK03/K03008.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Camshaft bushing removal pull direction (partial crankcase cut-away)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front of engine</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front and rear camshaft bushings</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Intermediate camshaft bushings</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft seal ring</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the camshaft seal ring from the back of the crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the expanding collet collapsed, install the collet assembly in the camshaft bushing and
                tighten backup nut until the collet fits the camshaft bushing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble the Camshaft Bushing Puller and install extension tube on the puller screw
                extension.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure pulling spacer is squarely mounted on the crankcase before tightening pulling nut.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Hold the end of the puller screw with a wrench and tighten the pulling nut against the
                thrust bearing and pulling plate until the camshaft bushing is removed.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front and rear camshaft bushings and then remove the two intermediate bushings.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
